'''Michael Gregoritsch''' (born 18 April 1994) is an Austrian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC Augsburg]], on loan from [[Danish Superliga]] club [[Brøndby IF|Brøndby]], and the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]].<ref name="kicker">{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.kicker.de/michael-gregoritsch/spieler/bundesliga/2024-25/sc-freiburg|language=de|title=Michael Gregoritsch|magazine=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]]|publisher=Olympia Vertlag GmbH|access-date=20 June 2015|archive-date=16 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150716201000/http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/2bundesliga/vereine/2014-15/63799/vereinsspieler_gregoritsch-michael.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kleinezeitung.at/sport/fussball/ksv/2334782/duo-gregoritsch.story|title = Das Gregoritsch-Märchen|newspaper=[[Kleine Zeitung]]|publisher=[[Styria Media Group]]|date=15 April 2010|access-date=25 January 2013|language=de|archive-date = 4 April 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120404142949/http://www.kleinezeitung.at/sport/fussball/ksv/2334782/duo-gregoritsch.story|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="bundesliga.at">{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesliga.at/index.php?id=20143&season=20112012&player=852091|language=de|title=Michael Gregoritsch|website=[[Austrian Football Bundesliga]]|access-date=25 May 2014|archive-date=23 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923195441/http://www.bundesliga.at/index.php?id=20143&season=20112012&player=852091|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career in Austria===
In 2008, Gregoritsch began his career at [[Kapfenberger SV]]'s youth teams and was promoted to the [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] team in January 2010.<ref name="merkur-online.de">{{cite web | url = http://www.merkur-online.de/sport/fussball/15-jaehriger-sein-erstes-bundesliga-tor-718158.html | title = 15-Jähriger erzielt Bundesliga-Tor|website=Merkur Online|date = 16 April 2010|access-date = 25 January 2013|language=de|archive-date = 1 October 2011|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111001042701/http://www.merkur-online.de/sport/fussball/15-jaehriger-sein-erstes-bundesliga-tor-718158.html | url-status = live }}</ref> He made his debut on 14 April 2010 against [[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]] and scored his first league goal less than three minutes after coming on as an 82nd-minute substitute.<ref name="merkur-online.de" /> This made him the youngest goalscorer in the history of the Austrian Bundesliga with only 15 years and 361 days.<ref name="kicker-2010-04-16">{{Cite magazine| url = https://www.kicker.de/gregoritsch-verzueckt-oesterreich-523767/artikel | title = Gregoritsch verzückt Österreich|magazine=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]]|publisher=Olympia Vertlag GmbH|date = 16 April 2010 | access-date = 25 January 2013 | archive-date = 10 October 2012 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121010202157/http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/intligen/startseite/523767/artikel_Gregoritsch-verzueckt-Oesterreich.html | url-status = live }}</ref> He finished the [[2009–10 Austrian Football Bundesliga|2009–10 season]] with a goal in four appearances.<ref name="Michael Gregoritsch » Club matches">{{cite web |title=Michael Gregoritsch {{!}} Club matches |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe173268/michael-gregoritsch/club-matches/|website=World Football|publisher=Heim: Spiel|access-date=3 September 2018 |archive-date=3 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903215339/https://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/michael-gregoritsch/2/ |url-status=live }}</ref> Gregoritsch also made appearances for the reserve team over three seasons.<ref name="2009–10 Landesliga Steiermark season">{{cite web|url=http://www.fussballoesterreich.at/foes/Home/?s=%2Fnetzwerk%2Fspielerdetails%2F670725461856634215_100094~581448932955043978~3.htm|language=de|title=Spielerprofil: Michael Gregoritsch - Kapfenberger SV Amateure 2009/10|website=Austrian Bundesliga|access-date=25 May 2014|archive-date=20 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620141439/http://www.fussballoesterreich.at/foes/Home/?s=%2Fnetzwerk%2Fspielerdetails%2F670725461856634215_100094~581448932955043978~3.htm|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="2010–11 Landesliga Steiermark season">{{cite web|url=http://www.fussballoesterreich.at/foes/Home/?s=%2Fnetzwerk%2Fspielerdetails%2F670725461856634215_100094~660029750971645857~3.htm|language=de|title=Spielerprofil: Michael Gregoritsch {{!}} Kapfenberger SV Amateure 2010/11|website=Austrian Bundesliga|access-date=25 May 2014|archive-date=20 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620141508/http://www.fussballoesterreich.at/foes/Home/?s=%2Fnetzwerk%2Fspielerdetails%2F670725461856634215_100094~660029750971645857~3.htm|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="2011–12 Regionalliga season">{{cite web|url=http://www.fussballoesterreich.at/foes/Home/?s=%2Fnetzwerk%2Fspielerdetails%2F670725461856634215_100094~743799140468038257~3.htm|language=de|title=Spielerprofil: Michael Gregoritsch - Kapfenberger SV Amateure 2011/12|publisher=Austrian Bundesliga|access-date=25 May 2014|archive-date=20 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620140815/http://www.fussballoesterreich.at/foes/Home/?s=%2Fnetzwerk%2Fspielerdetails%2F670725461856634215_100094~743799140468038257~3.htm|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Germany arrival===
Gregoritsch moved to [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]] on 28 June 2011 for an undisclosed fee. He signed a four-year contract but was on loan to Kapfenberger SV until June 2012. Gregoritsch only played for the second team of Hoffenheim, where he scored 11 goals in 28 appearances.<ref name="2012–13 season">{{Cite magazine|title=Michael Gregoritsch |url=https://www.kicker.de/gregoritsch-michael-63799/spieler/1-bundesliga/2012-13/1899-hoffenheim-3209|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222111331/https://www.kicker.de/gregoritsch-michael-63799/spieler/1-bundesliga/2012-13/1899-hoffenheim-3209|url-status=dead|archive-date=22 December 2019|magazine=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]]|publisher=Olympia Vertlag GmbH|access-date=3 September 2018 |language=de}}</ref> In 2013, he was on loan to [[FC St. Pauli]], playing for both the first and second teams.<ref name="Michael Gregoritsch » Club matches"/> Gregoritsch joined [[VfL Bochum]] on loan for the [[2014–15 VfL Bochum season|2014–15 season]],<ref name="Michael Gregoritsch » Club matches"/> where he scored seven goals in 27 appearances.<ref name="kicker"/> He played for [[Hamburger SV]] during the [[2015–16 Hamburger SV season|2015–16]] and [[2016–17 Hamburger SV season|2016–17]] seasons.<ref name="Michael Gregoritsch » Club matches"/> He scored six goals in 26 appearances during the 2015–16 season<ref name="2015–16 season">{{Cite magazine|title=Michael Gregoritsch |url=https://www.kicker.de/gregoritsch-michael-63799/spieler/2-bundesliga/2015-16/hamburger-sv-12 |magazine=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]]|publisher=Olympia Vertlag GmbH|access-date=3 September 2018 |language=de |archive-date=22 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222111336/https://www.kicker.de/gregoritsch-michael-63799/spieler/2-bundesliga/2015-16/hamburger-sv-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and five goals in 32 appearances during the 2016–17 season.<ref name="2016–17 season">{{cite magazine|title=Michael Gregoritsch |url=https://www.kicker.de/gregoritsch-michael-63799/spieler/2-bundesliga/2016-17/hamburger-sv-12 |magazine=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]]|publisher=Olympia Vertlag GmbH|access-date=3 September 2018 |language=de |archive-date=22 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222111333/https://www.kicker.de/gregoritsch-michael-63799/spieler/2-bundesliga/2016-17/hamburger-sv-12 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

Gregoritsch joined FC Augsburg for the [[2017–18 FC Augsburg season|2017–18 season]], scoring three goals in 33 appearances.<ref name="2017–18 season">{{cite web |title=Michael Gregoritsch 2017–18|url=https://www.kicker.de/michael-gregoritsch/spieler/bundesliga/2017-18/fc-augsburg |magazine=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|Kicker]]|publisher=Olympia Vertlag GmbH|access-date=3 September 2018 |language=de |archive-date=22 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222111335/https://www.kicker.de/gregoritsch-michael-63799/spieler/1-bundesliga/2017-18/fc-augsburg-91 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 23 December 2019, he joined [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] on loan until the end of 2019–20 season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/michael-gregoritsch-joins-fc-schalke-04-loan/|title=Michael Gregoritsch joins FC Schalke 04 on loan|website=Schalke 04|date=23 December 2019|access-date=23 December 2019|archive-date=23 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223134450/https://schalke04.de/en/team/michael-gregoritsch-joins-fc-schalke-04-loan/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 17 January 2020, Gregoritsch debuted with a goal and an assist in a 2–0 home victory against [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51157631|title=Borussia Monchengladbach dealt Bundesliga title blow by Schalke|website=[[BBC Sport]]|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=17 January 2020|access-date=18 January 2020|archive-date=18 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200118192146/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51157631|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 8 July 2022, Gregoritsch signed for [[SC Freiburg]] ahead of the [[2022–23 Bundesliga|2022–23]] Bundesliga season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scfreiburg.com/en/latest/news/first-team/20222023/michael-gregoritsch-joins-sc-freiburg/|title=Gregoritsch Joins SC Freiburg|website=SC Freiburg|date=8 July 2022|access-date=14 July 2022|archive-date=8 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220708205046/https://www.scfreiburg.com/en/latest/news/first-team/20222023/michael-gregoritsch-joins-sc-freiburg/|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Brøndby ===
On 20 August 2025, Gregoritsch joined [[Brøndby IF|Brøndby]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Brøndby IF |url=https://brondby.com/nyheder/herrer/2025/august/brondby-if-henter-michael-gregoritsch |title=Brøndby IF henter Michael Gregoritsch |date=20 August 2025 |access-date=7 October 2025 |language=da |trans-title=Brøndby IF signs Michael Gregoritsch}}</ref> He debuted the following day, coming on for [[Filip Bundgaard]] in the 67th minute of a 0–0 draw away to [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]] in the [[UEFA Europa Conference League]] play-off first leg.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.talksport.com/football/europa-conference-league/match/2025-08-21/strasbourg-v-brondby |title=Strasbourg v Brøndby – live updates |website=TalkSPORT |date=21 August 2025 |access-date=7 October 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/756261/br%C3%B8ndby-if-strasbourg |title=Strasbourg 0–0 Brøndby |website=ESPN |date=21 August 2025 |access-date=7 October 2025}}</ref> Three days later he made his [[Danish Superliga]] debut as a starter in a 2–0 defeat away to [[Sønderjyske Fodbold|Sønderjyske]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wehlast |first1=Mads Glenn |title=Birk sparer fem: Gregoritsch får første start |url=https://ekstrabladet.dk/sport/fodbold/dansk_fodbold/superligaen/birk-sparer-fem-gregoritsch-faar-foerste-start/10920792 |access-date=7 October 2025 |work=Ekstra Bladet |date=24 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250929091749/https://ekstrabladet.dk/sport/fodbold/dansk_fodbold/superligaen/birk-sparer-fem-gregoritsch-faar-foerste-start/10920792 |archive-date=29 September 2025 |language=da |trans-title=Birk makes five changes as Gregoritsch earns first start}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Roth |first1=Christopher |title=Brøndby taber og misser førsteplads |url=https://sport.tv2.dk/live/fodbold/2025-08-24-broendby-taber-og-misser-foersteplads |access-date=7 October 2025 |work=TV 2 Sport |date=24 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250825000512/https://sport.tv2.dk/live/fodbold/2025-08-24-broendby-taber-og-misser-foersteplads |archive-date=25 August 2025 |language=da-DK |trans-title=Brøndby lose and miss out on first place}}</ref> His first Brøndby goal followed in the second leg against Strasbourg on 28 August, making it 3–2 on the night when he converted an indirect free-kick from close range in the 85th minute; Brøndby were eliminated 2–3 on aggregate despite the late rally.<ref>{{cite news |title=Emegha and Doukouré fire Strasbourg into Europe! |url=https://ligue1.com/en/articles/l1_article_3116-emegha-and-doukoure-fire-strasbourg-into-europe |access-date=7 October 2025 |work=Ligue 1 |date=28 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251007092128/https://ligue1.com/en/articles/l1_article_3116-emegha-and-doukoure-fire-strasbourg-into-europe |archive-date=7 October 2025}}</ref>

On 7 January 2026, Gregoritsch returned to [[FC Augsburg]] on a six-month loan.<ref>{{cite press release |title=Michael Gregoritsch udlejes til FC Augsburg |url=https://brondby.com/nyheder/herrer/2026/januar/michael-gregoritsch-udlejes-til-fc-augsburg |website=Brøndby IF |access-date=8 January 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260108204924/https://brondby.com/nyheder/herrer/2026/januar/michael-gregoritsch-udlejes-til-fc-augsburg |archive-date=8 January 2026 |language=da |date=7 January 2026 |trans-title=Michael Gregoritsch loaned to FC Augsburg}}</ref>

==International career==
On 6 September 2016, Gregoritsch debuted for the [[Austria national football team|Austria national team]] in a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] against [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]], coming as a substitute to [[Marc Janko]] as Austria won 2–1.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Österreich siegt bei Gregoritsch-Debüt mit 2–1 in Georgien|trans-title=Austria wins 2–1 in Georgia on Gregoritsch's debut|url=https://www.abendblatt.de/sport/article208190307/Oesterreich-siegt-bei-Gregoritsch-Debuet-mit-2-1-in-Georgien.html|newspaper=[[Hamburger Abendblatt]]|publisher=[[Funke Mediengruppe]]|date=6 September 2016|access-date=23 November 2024|language=de}}</ref> On 27 March 2018, he scored his first goal in a 4–0 away win over [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] in a friendly match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fcaugsburg.de/en/article/michael-gregoritsch-scores-first-international-goal-4307 |title=Michael Gregoritsch scores first international goal |publisher=FC Augsburg |date=28 March 2018 }}</ref>

In May 2021, he was named in the Austrian squad for the postponed [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/Franco-Foda-fixiert-26-Spieler-umfassenden-EURO-Kader |title=Franco Foda fixiert 26 Spieler umfassenden EURO-Kader |trans-title=Franco Foda fixes the 26-player Euro squad |work=[[Austrian Football Association]] |date=24 May 2021 |access-date=24 May 2021 |language=de}}</ref> On 13 June 2021, he netted a goal in a 3–1 victory over [[North Macedonia national football team|North Macedonia]], helping secure Austria's first-ever European Championship win.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/history/news/026a-1282fa004ca4-e6cd5ea87d85-1000--austria-record-first-euro-win/ |title=Austria 3-1 North Macedonia: Arnautović caps first Austrian win |publisher=UEFA |date=13 June 2021 }}</ref>

In June 2024, Gregoritsch was called up for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=Nationalteam-Kader für UEFA Euro 2024 fixiert |trans-title=Final national team squad for UEFA Euro 2024 |url=https://www.oefb.at/oefb/News/OeFB-Kader-UEFA-EURO-2024 |language=de |publisher=[[Austrian Football Association]] |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> On 18 November 2025, he scored the equalizer in a 1–1 home draw against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]], sealing his nation's place at the top of [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|Group H]] and securing qualification for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] for the first time since 1998.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/austria-qualify-2026-world-cup-with-1-1-draw-against-bosnia-2025-11-18/ |title=Austria qualify for 2026 World Cup with 1-1 draw against Bosnia |publisher=Reuters |date=18 November 2025 }}</ref>

==Personal life==
As of July 2023, his father, [[Werner Gregoritsch]], is head coach of the Austrian under-21 national team. They are of [[Slovenes|Slovenian]] origin.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sueddeutsche.de/s5t38l/3312518/Trainersohn-15-trifft.html|title=In Österreichs erster Liga Trainersohn, 15 trifft|url-status=dead|newspaper= [[Süddeutsche Zeitung]]|access-date = 25 January 2013|language=de|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120401180419/http://www.sueddeutsche.de/s5t38l/3312518/Trainersohn-15-trifft.html|archive-date=1 April 2012}}</ref>

